text: In number theory, the harmonic numbers are the sums of the inverses of integers, forming the harmonic series. Harmonic number may also refer to: * Harmonic, a periodic wave with a frequency that is an integral multiple of the frequency of another wave * An integer not divisible by any prime other than 2 or 3, as defined by Philippe de Vitry * Harmonic divisor numbers, also called Ore numbers or Ore's harmonic numbers, positive integers whose divisors have an integral harmonic mean
title: Harmonic number (disambiguation)
